init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the “Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: ou and the rest of the “Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The drug was not as effective as the scientists thought, and it only stopped the aging process, not the aging itself.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The drug was recalled and the governments around the world started to monitor the drug users, and the drug was no longer distributed.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: and you have been living your life as normal as possible.
